---
import ServiceLayout from '../../../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import RelatedServices from '../../../../components/RelatedServices.astro';

const pageData = {
  title: "MOA Translation Dubai | MOJ Certified",
  description: "MOJ certified Memorandum of Association translation in Dubai. Mainland and Freezone MOA, share structure translation, DED licensing support.",
  keywords: "MOA translation dubai, memorandum of association translation, MOJ certified MOA, freezone MOA translation, mainland MOA translation",
  heroTitle: "Memorandum of Association Translation in Dubai",
  heroSubtitle: "MOJ Certified for Company Formation",
  heroIntro: "Your Memorandum of Association defines your company's structure, ownership, and operations. Whether you are opening a bank account, applying for additional licenses, or working with government authorities, the MOA translation must accurately reflect your company's legal status. We handle both mainland DED companies and free zone entities with the appropriate terminology for each regulatory context.",
  snapshot: [
    { icon: "clock", bold: "Digital drafts", text: "typically within 60 minutes" },
    { icon: "mobile-alt", bold: "WhatsApp-based workflow", text: "for easy communication" },
    { icon: "check-circle", bold: "Accepted by banks & DED", text: "for licensing" },
    { icon: "stamp", bold: "MOJ legal stamp", text: "with QR verification" }
  ],
  breadcrumbs: [
    { name: "Home", url: "/" },
    { name: "Legal", url: "/legal/" },
    { name: "Corporate", url: "/legal/corporate/" },
    { name: "MOA Translation", url: "/legal/corporate/moa/" }
  ],
  
  trustStrip: [
    "MOJ-licensed partner",
    "All free zones covered",
    "WhatsApp concierge support"
  ],
  
  processSteps: [
    {
      title: "Send your MOA document",
      text: "Include all pages, schedules, and any amendments. Specify if mainland or free zone company."
    },
    {
      title: "We prepare your translation",
      text: "MOJ-licensed translator handles corporate terminology and share structures accurately."
    },
    {
      title: "Pickup or delivery",
      text: "Collect in Dubai or arrange courier. Digital PDF sent immediately upon completion."
    }
  ],
  
  benefitCards: [
    {
      icon: "briefcase",
      title: "Mainland expertise",
      text: "DED company formation documents translated with proper Commercial Companies Law terminology."
    },
    {
      icon: "building",
      title: "Free zone coverage",
      text: "DMCC, JAFZA, DIFC, ADGM, and all other UAE free zones. Authority-specific formatting."
    },
    {
      icon: "document",
      title: "Share structure clarity",
      text: "Partner percentages, capital contributions, and profit distribution accurately rendered."
    }
  ],
  
  accordionSections: [
    {
      title: "Types of MOA we translate",
      id: "moa-types",
      items: [
        {
          heading: "Mainland MOA (DED registered)",
          body: "<p>Mainland companies registered with the Department of Economic Development follow UAE Commercial Companies Law requirements. The MOA includes specific articles about capital structure, partner obligations, profit distribution, and management authority.</p><p>We use terminology recognized by DED and UAE courts to ensure the translation serves its purpose in official proceedings. See our <a href='/services/legal-translation/'>legal translation services</a> for court-ready documents.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Free zone MOA",
          body: "<p>Free zone MOAs are governed by the respective free zone authority and often follow different templates with provisions specific to that zone's regulations. Each authority has preferred terminology and formatting.</p><p>We translate for all UAE free zones including DMCC, JAFZA, RAKEZ, SHAMS, and others.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "DIFC and ADGM documents",
          body: "<p>Common law free zones like <a href='/locations/dubai/difc/'>DIFC</a> and ADGM use different corporate structures including companies limited by shares, limited liability partnerships, and other forms. The documents follow English common law conventions.</p><p>We handle Articles of Association, Shareholders' Agreements, and other corporate governance documents for these jurisdictions.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Amended and restated MOA",
          body: "<p>If your MOA has been amended since initial formation, we translate the current consolidated version. If you need translation of both the original and amendments separately, we can provide that as a package.</p>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      title: "Where you will use your MOA translation",
      id: "use-cases",
      items: [
        {
          heading: "Bank account opening",
          body: "<p>UAE banks require MOA translations as part of corporate account opening. The translation must clearly show company ownership, authorized signatories, and capital structure.</p><p>For personal banking documents, see our <a href='/personal/immigration/bank/'>bank statement translation</a> services.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Additional licensing",
          body: "<p>When applying for additional trade licenses or expanding business activities, authorities need to verify your existing company structure. A certified MOA translation supports these applications.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Government tenders and contracts",
          body: "<p>Many government entities and large corporations require translated MOAs as part of vendor registration or tender submissions. The translation demonstrates your company's legal standing and structure.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Investor due diligence",
          body: "<p>Investors reviewing your company need to understand the corporate structure. A certified translation of the MOA provides clarity on ownership percentages, voting rights, and governance provisions. For <a href='/services/golden-visa-translation/'>Golden Visa investor applications</a>, additional documents may be needed.</p>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      title: "Related corporate documents",
      id: "related",
      items: [
        {
          heading: "Powers of Attorney",
          body: "<p>Company officers often need <a href='/legal/corporate/poa/'>Power of Attorney translation</a> for delegating authority to managers or agents. We handle both General and Special POAs.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Corporate translation services",
          body: "<p>For ongoing corporate documentation needs, see our comprehensive <a href='/services/corporate-translation/'>corporate translation services</a> covering all business documents including NDAs and shareholder agreements.</p>"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  
  faqs: [
    {
      question: "What is the difference between a Mainland MOA and a Freezone MOA?",
      answer: "A Mainland MOA is registered with DED and follows UAE Commercial Companies Law, with specific provisions about capital, partners, and profit distribution. Freezone MOAs are governed by the respective free zone authority with provisions specific to that zone. We adapt translation terminology to match the regulatory context of your company structure."
    },
    {
      question: "Is this translation accepted for bank account opening?",
      answer: "Yes. Our MOJ-certified MOA translations are accepted by all major UAE banks for corporate account opening. The translation includes all elements banks require: ownership structure, authorized signatories, capital details, and the official MOJ stamp."
    },
    {
      question: "Do you translate MOA amendments separately?",
      answer: "We can translate your current consolidated MOA, or we can translate the original MOA plus each amendment separately, depending on your needs. Let us know how the documents will be used and we will advise on the appropriate approach."
    },
    {
      question: "How long does MOA translation take?",
      answer: "Standard service delivers within 24 hours for typical MOAs. Express service completes in 6 hours. Complex MOAs with multiple schedules or lengthy shareholder agreements may require additional time, which we confirm upfront."
    },
    {
      question: "Can you translate MOAs from other countries?",
      answer: "Yes. We translate corporate formation documents from companies registered in any country. Foreign MOAs typically need attestation for use in the UAE. We verify attestation status during our pre-validation review."
    }
  ],
  serviceType: "Memorandum of Association Translation"
};
---

<ServiceLayout {...pageData}>
  
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What You Receive</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">Every MOA translation includes:</p>
      
      <div class="deliverables-grid">
        <div class="deliverable-card">
          <div class="deliverable-icon"><i class="fas fa-file-pdf"></i></div>
          <h3>Digital PDF Copy</h3>
          <p>Sent via WhatsApp and email. Suitable for initial bank submissions and internal review.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="deliverable-card">
          <div class="deliverable-icon"><i class="fas fa-stamp"></i></div>
          <h3>MOJ-Stamped Original</h3>
          <p>Physical copy with official stamp, QR verification, and translator license details.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="deliverable-card">
          <div class="deliverable-icon"><i class="fas fa-copy"></i></div>
          <h3>Certified Copies</h3>
          <p>Additional copies for multiple banks, government submissions, or investor packages.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="deliverable-card">
          <div class="deliverable-icon"><i class="fas fa-truck"></i></div>
          <h3>Courier Delivery</h3>
          <p>Free delivery across Dubai. Next-day delivery to other Emirates.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Service Levels and Pricing</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">Pricing depends on document length and complexity:</p>
      
      <div class="pricing-grid">
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <h3>Standard</h3>
          <div class="pricing-price">From AED 250</div>
          <p class="pricing-time">24-hour delivery</p>
          <ul class="pricing-features">
            <li>MOJ-certified translation</li>
            <li>Digital PDF + physical copy</li>
            <li>Free Dubai delivery</li>
            <li>WhatsApp updates</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="pricing-card pricing-card--featured">
          <h3>Express</h3>
          <div class="pricing-price">From AED 400</div>
          <p class="pricing-time">6-hour delivery</p>
          <ul class="pricing-features">
            <li>Everything in Standard</li>
            <li>Priority queue</li>
            <li>Dedicated coordinator</li>
            <li>Same-day physical delivery</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <h3>VIP Concierge</h3>
          <div class="pricing-price">From AED 600</div>
          <p class="pricing-time">Rush processing</p>
          <ul class="pricing-features">
            <li>Everything in Express</li>
            <li>Immediate agent assignment</li>
            <li>Direct phone line</li>
            <li>Bank coordination support</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <RelatedServices
        pageKey="moa"
        title="Related Corporate Documents"
        showFamily={true}
        showNextSteps={true}
        showCrossSilo={true}
        maxItems={6}
      />
    </div>
  </section>

</ServiceLayout>

<style>
  .section-intro {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    max-width: 700px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  
  .deliverables-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .deliverable-card {
    background: #f8f9fa;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .deliverable-icon {
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: var(--primary-color);
    color: #ffffff;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  
  .deliverable-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }
  
  .deliverable-card p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  
  .pricing-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .pricing-card {
    background: #ffffff;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .pricing-card--featured {
    border-color: var(--accent-color);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(255, 22, 84, 0.15);
  }
  
  .pricing-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }
  
  .pricing-price {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--primary-color);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  
  .pricing-time {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .pricing-features {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    text-align: left;
  }
  
  .pricing-features li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
  }
  
  .pricing-features li::before {
    content: 'âœ“';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent-color);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
</style>
